1
00:00:13,330 --> 00:00:15,990
Ji Sung

2
00:00:18,750 --> 00:00:21,360
Kim Min Jung

3
00:00:24,750 --> 00:00:27,380
Jin Young

4
00:00:32,290 --> 00:00:34,620
Park Gyu Young

5
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:39,200
NO JUSTICE

6
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:50,490
Devil Judge

7
00:00:50,490 --> 00:00:55,560
This is a virtual dystopia (imaginary society with great injustice) set in Korea. All characters, organizations, events, etc. are fictional.

8
00:00:59,260 --> 00:01:01,860
Do work that suits you.

9
00:01:03,790 --> 00:01:06,450
I heard you were a maid originally?

10
00:01:09,580 --> 00:01:11,590
Jeez, what a beggar-like...

11
00:01:18,660 --> 00:01:19,820
Yes, Eonni?

12
00:01:19,820 --> 00:01:22,790
Kang Yo Han leaked information about me to Cha Gyeong Hui.

13
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:24,600
- What did you say?
- Find out.

14
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:25,940
Don't tell me Kang Yo Han—

15
00:01:25,940 --> 00:01:28,740
Shut up and find out right now!

16
00:01:31,290 --> 00:01:34,100
If you interfere with my work, you will pay the price.

17
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:36,930
It seems you've been working pretty hard to get where you are.

18
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:38,680
Will it be all right with you?

19
00:02:00,930 --> 00:02:03,250
I'm going to kill him.

20
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:10,690
Kang Yo Han, I'm going to rip you apart.

21
00:02:23,050 --> 00:02:26,190
But isn't that too dangerous?
 Episode 11

22
00:02:26,190 --> 00:02:28,360
You said she was an unpredictable person.

23
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:33,890
I told you. If the world's rulers are united, there's no way to do it.

24
00:02:33,890 --> 00:02:35,710
We've secured Do Yeong Chun.

25
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:37,650
We'll use him to catch Cha Gyeong Hui first–

26
00:02:37,650 --> 00:02:41,370
You want me to report it to the prosecution? Or tell the press?

27
00:02:44,020 --> 00:02:47,950
Cha Gyeong Hui has files on the corruption of media owners.

28
00:02:47,950 --> 00:02:50,680
It's impossible to take them down from the outside,

29
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:54,000
so we have no choice but to make them point the sword at each other.

30
00:02:55,090 --> 00:02:57,640
And then what if the sword is turned towards you?

31
00:02:57,640 --> 00:03:00,770
How can I win the game without betting anything on it?

32
00:03:00,770 --> 00:03:04,080
Fortunately, there's at least one place that hurts

33
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:07,510
when a human being is stabbed.

34
00:03:08,590 --> 00:03:10,410
For anyone.

35
00:03:20,090 --> 00:03:22,700
Did you eat dinner?

36
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:24,470
How's Yeong Min?

37
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:26,850
Oh, he's the same today.

38
00:03:26,850 --> 00:03:29,790
The wound's almost healed.

39
00:03:29,790 --> 00:03:31,590
Even so...

40
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:37,190
Mom, let's go to the US.

41
00:03:37,190 --> 00:03:40,380
I don't think I can live here.

42
00:03:40,380 --> 00:03:43,590
Mom, it's because I'm scared.

43
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:45,980
Come with me, okay?

44
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,970
Get up.

45
00:03:48,970 --> 00:03:52,560
- Mom.
- I said get up. Get up.

46
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,740
Can you not hear me?

47
00:03:55,410 --> 00:03:57,350
Get up!

48
00:03:59,580 --> 00:04:02,750
- You're such a weak bastard!
- Honey.

49
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:05,360
You didn't think to pay me back, and you want to escape?!

50
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:07,910
After you suffered this humiliation, how can you...

51
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:12,170
How can you be such a loser?

52
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:28,630
How far does Cha Gyeong Hui's knowledge extend?

53
00:04:30,220 --> 00:04:33,900
I looked into it, but there's no connection between them.

54
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:39,150
They're like enemies, but did Cha Gyeong Hui hold hands with Kang Yo Han?

55
00:04:39,150 --> 00:04:41,400
It can only be Kang Yo Han.

56
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:45,870
He put a knife in Cha Gyeong Hui's hands and stabbed me in the back.

57
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:52,880
There's something he's after.

58
00:04:58,740 --> 00:05:02,390
Minister Cha Gyeong Hui

59
00:05:09,820 --> 00:05:12,070
Yes, Minister?

60
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:21,920
Investigation report on unnatural death.

61
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:26,380
You hid it well. You must have spent a lot of money.

62
00:05:26,380 --> 00:05:29,090
The mother, who beat her daughter when she was drunk,

63
00:05:29,090 --> 00:05:33,010
happened to die after she fell down the stairs in a mountain village.

64
00:05:33,010 --> 00:05:36,730
The security lights were off, and there was only one witness.

65
00:05:36,730 --> 00:05:39,840
That child's tearful acting was so good

66
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:45,720
that the cops had no doubt she slipped while in a drunken state and the case was closed.

67
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,770
Well, I think that was enough material.

68
00:05:49,770 --> 00:05:53,090
The only evidence that she was drunk was her daughter's statement.

69
00:05:53,090 --> 00:05:57,340
What if a completely contradictory doctor's note pops up?

70
00:05:57,340 --> 00:06:00,880
Saying there was no trace of alcohol in her body.

71
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:05,840
That it couldn't have happened without someone pushing her from behind.

72
00:06:07,790 --> 00:06:11,670
There was no such note, but–

73
00:06:11,670 --> 00:06:15,380
You still don't understand?

74
00:06:15,380 --> 00:06:20,500
That's the truth. I made it to be the truth.

75
00:06:21,250 --> 00:06:24,900
I just need something to stimulate the public's imagination.

76
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:27,360
You're definitely an expert.

77
00:06:27,980 --> 00:06:32,350
Fabricated evidence and coercive investigation are the Minister's speciality.

78
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:34,240
Thank you for the compliment.

79
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,940
What do you want?

80
00:06:35,940 --> 00:06:40,840
Kang You Han. Grab him and restore my son's honor.

81
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:42,720
Then I'll let you go.

82
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:45,540
It's a case where the trial is already done. How can I–

83
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:49,080
That's why I need someone like you.

84
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:54,560
Someone born and raised in dirty, muddy water, who would do anything to survive.

85
00:06:59,010 --> 00:07:03,920
I'll give you a week. Bring me what I want.

86
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:21,790
- You're here, Young Master.
- How have you been?

87
00:07:31,810 --> 00:07:33,920
Should I do the usual?

88
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,370
Yes.

89
00:07:36,970 --> 00:07:38,520
Sounds good.

90
00:08:38,180 --> 00:08:41,650
Hi, Young Master.

91
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:50,130
How did you get here?

92
00:08:52,660 --> 00:08:54,250
What about Ajeossi?

93
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:00,990
Don't tell me you–

94
00:09:00,990 --> 00:09:05,280
Don't get worked up. He's just sleeping for a moment.

95
00:09:06,890 --> 00:09:09,280
What are you up to?

96
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:13,550
I just always wanted to do this once.

97
00:09:13,550 --> 00:09:18,850
To make my young master look handsome.

98
00:09:24,450 --> 00:09:26,300
If it's your wish.

99
00:09:31,890 --> 00:09:34,110
By the way,

100
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:37,190
why did you do that?

101
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:38,990
What are you talking about?

102
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:42,460
I'm talking about you leaking my story to Cha Gyeong Hui.

103
00:09:42,460 --> 00:09:45,750
Thanks to you, I'm in a lot of trouble.

104
00:09:46,390 --> 00:09:48,660
Because I need you.

105
00:09:48,660 --> 00:09:50,690
Do you mean it?

106
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:53,590
I need to catch Cha Gyeong Hui.

107
00:09:53,590 --> 00:09:55,800
I'm saying I wanted you to do that too.

108
00:09:55,800 --> 00:10:00,090
So you put me in a corner?

109
00:10:03,990 --> 00:10:09,000
You are a really bad man.

110
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,220
You're shameless.

111
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:20,490
Isn't that why you like me? I'm like you.

112
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:26,460
It's irreversible anyway.

113
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,860
Now, as long as Cha Gyeong Hui is here,

114
00:10:30,490 --> 00:10:33,410
you can't be free.

115
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,790
You should make a choice.

116
00:10:46,590 --> 00:10:49,140
And what if I choose this blade?

117
00:10:49,950 --> 00:10:51,900
There is nothing I can do.

118
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:56,100
Do as you please.

119
00:11:12,550 --> 00:11:14,790
Do you want to go to my house?

120
00:11:19,090 --> 00:11:21,230
It's been awhile.

121
00:11:21,970 --> 00:11:25,630
It will remind us of the old days and sounds like fun.

122
00:13:58,270 --> 00:14:00,790
What are you thinking about?

123
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:09,580
Everything is the same.

124
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:16,400
You've changed.

125
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:20,520
Is that so?

126
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:22,810
How have I changed?

127
00:14:22,810 --> 00:14:24,710
Chairwoman.

128
00:14:27,830 --> 00:14:32,880
Welcome. I heard from the chief that he was going to invite you.

129
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:38,520
- Is that so?
- If you don't mind, let's have dinner together. It's dinner time.

130
00:14:58,680 --> 00:15:02,220
Did Judge Kim really make all of this?

131
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:05,120
- Since I'm a freeloader here.

132
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:09,100
Your wounds would have healed by now, no?

133
00:15:14,070 --> 00:15:17,930
I didn't know you had so many talents like this, Judge Kim.

134
00:15:17,930 --> 00:15:21,390
I didn't know either, when I first met you,

135
00:15:21,390 --> 00:15:24,460
that you had so many talents.

136
00:15:29,230 --> 00:15:34,570
- Who is she?
- She's the head of the live court's support team.

137
00:15:35,190 --> 00:15:38,450
But you've never brought a woman to this house. Are you two dating?

138
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:43,200
- Elijah.
- I'm honored. I guess I'm the first female guest.

139
00:15:43,260 --> 00:15:45,550
You're dating her, right?

140
00:15:45,550 --> 00:15:47,700
Shall we have dinner now?

141
00:15:49,580 --> 00:15:52,890
- I asked if you're dating.
- No we're not.

142
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:55,730
She's someone who's helping the chief.

143
00:15:55,730 --> 00:15:58,210
Please help him a lot from now on.

144
00:15:58,210 --> 00:16:03,490
I don't know whether I'm capable of helping Judge Kang.

145
00:16:03,490 --> 00:16:07,060
I heard from the chief that you are an essential person.

146
00:16:08,210 --> 00:16:12,740
I'm flattered. Did Judge Kang really say that?

147
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:15,460
Why are you talking such nonsense, huh?

148
00:16:15,460 --> 00:16:18,290
Let's just have dinner. You too.

149
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:21,400
Elijah, eat this first.

150
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:36,500
Judge Kim looks as if he's always been a member of this family.

151
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:39,250
You fit right in.

152
00:16:39,250 --> 00:16:41,010
Oh, is that so?

153
00:16:42,770 --> 00:16:45,730
You won't be lonely anymore.

154
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,750
I envy you.

155
00:16:55,050 --> 00:16:58,590
Did you two know each other before?

156
00:16:58,590 --> 00:17:03,100
We just support and cheer each other from behind, it's that kind of relationship.

157
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:05,320
Miss Elijah.

158
00:17:05,320 --> 00:17:08,330
How does she know my name?

159
00:17:08,330 --> 00:17:11,720
Shall we make a toast? We have an important guest.

160
00:17:19,790 --> 00:17:22,120
- You can't.
- Then what shall I toast with?

161
00:17:22,120 --> 00:17:24,130
You have juice.

162
00:17:24,840 --> 00:17:27,210
Thank you. Here!

163
00:17:27,210 --> 00:17:30,620
Wait a minute. It's time for someone to come.

164
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:35,930
What's the reason you asked me to come in the evening?

165
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:38,700
Oh, you had a guest.

166
00:17:39,950 --> 00:17:47,160
To Chairman Jeong Seon Ah, who has returned to our home after a long time.

167
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:51,220
If it's Seo... Seon Ah...

168
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:02,820
Are you playing with me right now?!

169
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:06,330
Didn't you like it? I'm sorry to hear that.

170
00:18:06,330 --> 00:18:10,730
I'm playing with you. You're fun.

171
00:18:11,730 --> 00:18:17,790
You're smart, relentless, and as broken as I am.

172
00:18:17,790 --> 00:18:20,870
That's very uncommon.

173
00:18:24,330 --> 00:18:28,510
I was thinking it would be fun to play with you.

174
00:18:28,510 --> 00:18:30,980
You suggested it first.

175
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:36,420
You told me to go to the top of the world,

176
00:18:37,140 --> 00:18:39,190
with you.

177
00:19:13,590 --> 00:19:15,610
Smile,

178
00:19:15,610 --> 00:19:19,590
you fit pretty well in this house.

179
00:19:32,320 --> 00:19:36,190
Will Jeong Seon Ah really take your hand?

180
00:19:36,190 --> 00:19:40,510
Maybe she'll be on Cha Gyeong Hui's side. She's so unpredictable.

181
00:19:41,290 --> 00:19:45,080
That's ridiculous. It's obvious it's a trick.

182
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:46,950
Right?

183
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:51,680
Kang Yo Han, who does he think you are? He's messing with you like this?

184
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:55,150
- I can't believe it.
- Yes.

185
00:19:55,150 --> 00:19:58,710
I know it's a trick, but

186
00:19:59,590 --> 00:20:03,490
he doesn't even try to hide it.

187
00:20:03,490 --> 00:20:05,730
So?

188
00:20:05,730 --> 00:20:08,560
It's weird.

189
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:11,410
I want to be fooled.

190
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:16,450
Even if it's just for a short time.

191
00:20:16,450 --> 00:20:18,710
Eonni!

192
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:24,850
I shouldn't, right? I knew it.

193
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:31,830
Oh Jin Ju

194
00:20:36,190 --> 00:20:37,870
Yes, this is Judge Oh Jin Ju.

195
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:39,920
Yes, I know.

196
00:20:40,830 --> 00:20:44,770
My name is Park Du Man, President of Saram Media Group.

197
00:20:44,770 --> 00:20:47,190
Ah, hello.

198
00:20:47,190 --> 00:20:49,980
I'm sorry to call you out of the blue.

199
00:20:49,980 --> 00:20:52,920
I wanted to meet with you once at our Social Responsibility Foundation.

200
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:55,800
Do you mean all of us from the live court?

201
00:20:55,800 --> 00:21:01,460
No, no. Judge Oh Jin Ju is the only one we want to meet.

202
00:21:04,020 --> 00:21:06,960
Sure.

203
00:21:12,860 --> 00:21:14,950
Is something wrong?

204
00:21:17,620 --> 00:21:19,590
It's nothing.

205
00:21:45,530 --> 00:21:47,910
Judge Oh, here you are.

206
00:21:55,070 --> 00:21:58,860
Have a seat over there.

207
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:18,000
It's nice to meet you. I'm Oh Jin Ju.

208
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,360
I enjoyed the promotional video for the live trial.

209
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:23,440
You were meant for it. You did a great job.

210
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:27,960
- Thank you.
- Please help us with our foundation.

211
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:31,030
- If it's a foundation job–
- It's all work for the nation.

212
00:22:31,030 --> 00:22:35,220
I need a face to deliver it to the public with confidence.

213
00:22:35,220 --> 00:22:37,350
You are so great,

214
00:22:37,350 --> 00:22:42,220
but there are a few things that are bothering me, so I asked you to come.

215
00:22:42,220 --> 00:22:44,760
I'm not sure I understand.

216
00:22:46,260 --> 00:22:51,690
When you were in a trial in the province, you put the owner of a business under court custody.

217
00:22:51,690 --> 00:22:55,260
Isn't a suspended sentence reasonable if someone spends some money from their own company?

218
00:22:55,260 --> 00:22:57,750
Why were you do hard on him?

219
00:22:57,750 --> 00:23:01,430
Do you have any anti-corporate sentiments?

220
00:23:04,690 --> 00:23:08,520
Is this, by any chance, a job interview?

221
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:10,390
I don't think you're picking a model.

222
00:23:10,390 --> 00:23:15,730
Is this an interview for the post of the presiding judge of the live court?

223
00:23:16,330 --> 00:23:18,790
You're quick to understand too.

224
00:23:18,790 --> 00:23:21,830
I would like to make you a national star,

225
00:23:21,830 --> 00:23:25,730
but shouldn't we find out what the risks are?

226
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:34,390
Did you also put Judge Kang Yo Han through this?

227
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:44,460
The Chief Justice of the Supreme Court has also been here.

228
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:26,420
Don't you think this is the proper distance to hold a conversation?

229
00:24:26,420 --> 00:24:29,720
What questions do you have about me?

230
00:24:38,050 --> 00:24:41,590
- I'm really skilled–
- It's falling down. It's falling down. Oh! It's falling down. It's falling down.

231
00:24:41,590 --> 00:24:44,290
Elijah, eat this.

232
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:50,880
Fall down. Fall down. Fall down. Fall down. Fall down.

233
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:59,690
Now it's Elijah's turn.

234
00:25:01,130 --> 00:25:03,130
Oh, my! How are you going to do this?

235
00:25:03,130 --> 00:25:05,220
I think it's going to fall.

236
00:25:05,220 --> 00:25:08,640
You got it. You got it.
- It's.. fall...ing Eli... Ah!

237
00:25:09,350 --> 00:25:10,970
Yes!

238
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:21,670
Chief, play with us... Chie... Chief.

239
00:25:21,670 --> 00:25:24,920
Forget it. Yo Han doesn't play games like this.

240
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:38,160
Chief, you had something to say, didn't you?

241
00:25:38,760 --> 00:25:40,650
Huh?

242
00:25:42,460 --> 00:25:44,600
I was just passing by.

243
00:25:51,190 --> 00:25:55,260
There's been something frightening about Kang Yo Han since then.

244
00:25:55,260 --> 00:25:56,630
Is that so?

245
00:25:56,630 --> 00:26:02,050
One time, I was playing with my friends and he was watching me in secret while mimicking me.

246
00:26:02,050 --> 00:26:05,050
Someone win!

247
00:26:05,050 --> 00:26:07,980
Someone win!

248
00:26:07,980 --> 00:26:10,420
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Yeah!

249
00:26:14,550 --> 00:26:18,690
Hey, don't you know how to put out paper? You idiot.

250
00:26:18,690 --> 00:26:20,550
- Why are you so bad at this?
- Ah, try to do better.

251
00:26:20,550 --> 00:26:22,530
I'm sorry.

252
00:26:22,530 --> 00:26:26,130
Seriously. Do it right the next round.

253
00:26:29,090 --> 00:26:31,840
It really creeped me out...

254
00:26:32,480 --> 00:26:34,440
But Father ...

255
00:26:36,040 --> 00:26:37,430
Yes?

256
00:26:38,300 --> 00:26:41,220
Couldn't it be he actually wanted to hang out with friends?

257
00:26:41,220 --> 00:26:44,530
Someone win!

258
00:26:44,530 --> 00:26:46,830
