00:47:05,850 --> 00:47:08,850
how can you block it if you have multiple shots flying at the same time?

513
00:47:08,850 --> 00:47:11,350
It won't be easy.

514
00:47:11,350 --> 00:47:14,360
We're just getting started.

515
00:47:14,970 --> 00:47:18,090
Tell me what you want from me!

516
00:47:18,090 --> 00:47:20,390
You set up a task force and

517
00:47:20,390 --> 00:47:24,100
did a background check on Heo Jung Se and the Foundation directors, right?

518
00:47:24,100 --> 00:47:26,900
Hand over these files to me.

519
00:47:26,900 --> 00:47:31,210
If you do that, I'll at least let you live.

520
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:35,230
At least let me live?

521
00:47:35,230 --> 00:47:38,830
Do you think I'm going to stand back and watch?

522
00:47:38,830 --> 00:47:42,920
How dare you.

523
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:44,860
Is that so?

524
00:47:45,510 --> 00:47:47,570
All right.

525
00:47:49,410 --> 00:47:52,330
If you change your mind, let me know.

526
00:48:24,480 --> 00:48:27,180
Honey, are you all right?

527
00:48:27,180 --> 00:48:29,460
What do we do about this?

528
00:48:29,460 --> 00:48:33,850
You're all over the news.

529
00:48:41,110 --> 00:48:43,230
I'm sorry, Mom.

530
00:48:43,230 --> 00:48:45,420
It's because of me.

531
00:48:47,810 --> 00:48:50,120
I'm sorry I did this.

532
00:48:52,180 --> 00:48:55,370
Both of you listen carefully.

533
00:48:57,630 --> 00:49:00,240
Don't ever show weakness.

534
00:49:00,240 --> 00:49:02,810
Only the weak will suffer.

535
00:49:02,810 --> 00:49:06,770
I will clench my teeth and hang on till the end

536
00:49:06,770 --> 00:49:09,540
and make them end up on their knees.

537
00:49:11,060 --> 00:49:13,960
How did I get here?

538
00:49:13,960 --> 00:49:17,400
That's right, Honey, you will get through this.

539
00:49:17,400 --> 00:49:19,880
You are a strong person.

540
00:49:21,420 --> 00:49:23,450
Sorry.

541
00:49:25,230 --> 00:49:29,290
I know how hard you worked to get where you are.

542
00:49:29,290 --> 00:49:31,280
I'm sorry.

543
00:49:35,260 --> 00:49:37,700
Don't give her a break and push through.

544
00:49:37,700 --> 00:49:40,990
She's someone that will abandon her child for her ambitions.

545
00:49:40,990 --> 00:49:43,420
She won't give up easily.

546
00:49:43,420 --> 00:49:48,520
Well, I'm glad I went through Cha Gyeong Hui's old investigation records.

547
00:49:49,170 --> 00:49:51,560
Thank you, Judge Kim.

548
00:49:51,560 --> 00:49:56,370
No. You had a hard time looking for each and every victim.

549
00:49:56,370 --> 00:49:59,890
It's not over yet. Don't waste time on idle talk.

550
00:49:59,890 --> 00:50:01,800
What about the prison warden of the prison? Is it settled?

551
00:50:01,800 --> 00:50:05,820
Yes, I've scared him enough to do anything he's told.

552
00:50:05,820 --> 00:50:08,360
I've also gave orders to Cha Gyeong Hui's secretary.

553
00:50:08,360 --> 00:50:10,620
So that you can handle it quietly.

554
00:50:10,620 --> 00:50:14,480
If this goes according to plan, she will end up falling apart.

555
00:50:15,280 --> 00:50:17,750
At that moment, you have to reach out

556
00:50:17,750 --> 00:50:20,280
so that she clings on to you to do anything to survive.

557
00:50:20,280 --> 00:50:22,690
The Minister is here!

558
00:50:26,710 --> 00:50:29,200
Minister, did you really switch out Do Yeong Chun?

559
00:50:29,200 --> 00:50:30,800
What about coercing the false statement?

560
00:50:30,800 --> 00:50:37,250
Minister, about Do Yeong Chun–

561
00:50:37,250 --> 00:50:40,880
The truth will be revealed through the prosecution.

562
00:50:40,880 --> 00:50:43,360
Minister, tell us the reason.

563
00:50:43,360 --> 00:50:46,430
Minister, please say something!

564
00:50:46,430 --> 00:50:49,740
- Minister!
- Minister!

565
00:50:49,740 --> 00:50:52,310
Tell us the reason.

566
00:50:52,310 --> 00:50:55,480
Please tell us the reason, Minister.

567
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:58,470
Minister, tell us the reason.

568
00:51:02,700 --> 00:51:07,310
Your broadcast station is biting me the most relentlessly. Are you out of your mind?

569
00:51:07,310 --> 00:51:12,560
Oh my, Minister. Do young reporters listen to their superiors these days?

570
00:51:12,560 --> 00:51:16,840
I don't know if it's journalism or anything. It's killing me. Us too.

571
00:51:18,140 --> 00:51:20,830
You son of a bitch.

572
00:51:20,830 --> 00:51:23,480
Minister, we are in trouble.

573
00:51:23,480 --> 00:51:25,520
What is it now?

574
00:51:25,520 --> 00:51:29,600
Just a moment ago, the head of the Gyeongi Nambu Prison, began a declaration of conscience, in front of reporters,

575
00:51:29,600 --> 00:51:34,260
regarding the replacement of Minister of Justice Cha Gyeong Hui's infamous scammer.

576
00:51:34,260 --> 00:51:37,860
Is it true that it was an order from the Minister of Justice?

577
00:51:37,860 --> 00:51:40,610
It's true that it was an order from Minister Cha Gyeong Hui.

578
00:51:40,610 --> 00:51:43,770
Is it true that you were bribed and threatened?

579
00:51:43,770 --> 00:51:47,700
I'm sorry. I could not stand her threats.

580
00:51:47,700 --> 00:51:53,810
That bastard. He said he'd do anything if I could get him promoted.

581
00:51:59,760 --> 00:52:04,360
Minister, this is the Central District Attorney's call.

582
00:52:04,360 --> 00:52:07,990
I think you need to show up at the District Attorney's Office.

583
00:52:07,990 --> 00:52:11,360
- What is it?
- There have been twelve complaints filed.

584
00:52:11,360 --> 00:52:15,430
The defendants of the cases you investigated and their families.

585
00:52:15,450 --> 00:52:19,270
Threatening, coercion, consequential damages, abuse of authority.

586
00:52:19,270 --> 00:52:21,870
It's not just one or two counts.

587
00:52:22,770 --> 00:52:29,020
Chief Prosecutor Kim, have you forgotten who put you in that position? Huh?

588
00:52:29,020 --> 00:52:31,420
I'm sorry, Minister.

589
00:52:31,420 --> 00:52:36,010
I don't think this will be easily covered up.

590
00:52:36,010 --> 00:52:39,500
Why don't you let matters run their course?

591
00:52:46,830 --> 00:52:50,180
- Get the car ready.
- Where do you want to go?

592
00:52:50,180 --> 00:52:52,570
To the Blue House.

593
00:52:58,780 --> 00:53:02,530
Eat some. Don't you like snacks?

594
00:53:02,530 --> 00:53:04,500
But how did this happen?

595
00:53:04,500 --> 00:53:07,070
You're someone who was set to be moving into this house two years from now.

596
00:53:07,070 --> 00:53:10,220
How the hell did you end up here?

597
00:53:10,220 --> 00:53:14,520
My wife and I were very careful with the furniture and things like that,

598
00:53:14,520 --> 00:53:17,650
keeping them without a scratch thinking of handing it to you.

599
00:53:17,650 --> 00:53:19,400
I'll just get to the point.

600
00:53:19,400 --> 00:53:23,380
No, no, no. Introduction, main point, conclusion, verse 1, verse 2, verse 3.

601
00:53:23,380 --> 00:53:28,220
You can tell me everything. We're not going to see each other again anyway.

602
00:53:29,810 --> 00:53:33,440
There's a file I have been collecting.

603
00:53:39,340 --> 00:53:43,430
- File?
- Secret funds from the last presidential election.

604
00:53:43,430 --> 00:53:47,710
As well as why the Gwanghwamun protests suddenly grew into a riot.

605
00:53:48,820 --> 00:53:55,090
Wow, wow this is just... you're breaking the game, aren't you?

606
00:53:55,090 --> 00:54:00,240
You think that someone who's going to be arrested right now can make such a big deal?

607
00:54:00,240 --> 00:54:04,320
- I'm not saying I'll do it.
- Then?

608
00:54:05,360 --> 00:54:08,730
I'm going to hand it over to Kang Yo Han.

609
00:54:12,460 --> 00:54:18,030
If you don't like that, stop all this at any cost.

610
00:54:18,030 --> 00:54:20,990
Whether it's mobilizing the National Intelligence Service, the military, or anything!

611
00:54:20,990 --> 00:54:25,560
Wait a minute. All right, all right. Wow, our Cha Gyeong Hui is coming on strong.

612
00:54:25,560 --> 00:54:30,120
But I have this weird handicap of being unable to make important decisions on my own.

613
00:54:30,120 --> 00:54:34,790
Wait a minute. Honey! Hey, honey!

614
00:54:36,560 --> 00:54:39,150
We have a guest.

615
00:54:39,150 --> 00:54:45,550
Yeong Min's mom, what's going on between us?

616
00:54:45,550 --> 00:54:47,970
What is this supposed to do?

617
00:54:47,970 --> 00:54:51,480
So let's talk as parents from now on.

618
00:54:51,480 --> 00:54:55,830
Yeong Min and our Jun Hui, they've been best friends since they were kids.

619
00:54:55,830 --> 00:55:00,630
Yes, Jun Hui was really worried about Yeong Min,

620
00:55:00,630 --> 00:55:05,250
because he was so lonely and sensitive.

621
00:55:07,350 --> 00:55:09,960
What are you trying to say?

622
00:55:12,020 --> 00:55:17,750
Yeong Min's mother, did you know

623
00:55:18,760 --> 00:55:22,910
that he's been on drugs since high school?

624
00:55:26,200 --> 00:55:29,860
Drugs are hard to stop once you touch them, right?

625
00:55:29,860 --> 00:55:34,320
I found that there isn't a single drug that Yeong Min hasn't taken.

626
00:55:34,320 --> 00:55:36,790
He's been taking a ton.

627
00:55:36,790 --> 00:55:42,330
Isn't that why he keeps going around doing crazy shit?

628
00:55:42,330 --> 00:55:45,710
So what are you going to do with Yeong Min? Huh?

629
00:55:45,710 --> 00:55:47,650
What do you mean what?

630
00:55:47,650 --> 00:55:52,180
The Republic of Korea is a country of rule of law, so we must follow that. You know the law, don't you?

631
00:55:52,200 --> 00:55:55,850
If he goes to prison, I think he'll be there for a long time. Will he be all right?

632
00:55:55,850 --> 00:56:01,590
From since he was young, wasn't he a weak kid from head to toe?

633
00:56:01,590 --> 00:56:03,710
I'm worried.

634
00:56:03,710 --> 00:56:06,750
And since getting flogged thanks to his mom,

635
00:56:06,750 --> 00:56:10,390
I heard he's become even more of a wimp.

636
00:56:10,390 --> 00:56:13,180
All moms would feel the same.

637
00:56:13,180 --> 00:56:16,850
One's self is the most important, isn't it?

638
00:56:16,850 --> 00:56:19,800
Think about it carefully, Yeong Min's Mom.

639
00:56:19,800 --> 00:56:24,040
Honey, look at this. The cup is about to break.

640
00:56:27,790 --> 00:56:31,680
Let go. It's about to break.

641
00:56:31,680 --> 00:56:37,230
Minister Cha, think rationally.

642
00:56:37,900 --> 00:56:40,260
For your child's sake.

643
00:56:54,600 --> 00:56:57,580
The conversation must not have gone well.

644
00:57:05,320 --> 00:57:09,460
Who are you? Where's Secretary Kim?

645
00:57:09,460 --> 00:57:12,480
Secretary Kim has quit.

646
00:57:15,040 --> 00:57:17,930
Who the hell are you to be in my car?

647
00:57:17,930 --> 00:57:21,490
I'm helping Judge Kang Yo Han.

648
00:57:23,000 --> 00:57:25,900
This is your last chance, Minister.

649
00:57:25,900 --> 00:57:28,360
Have you made up your mind?

650
00:57:29,380 --> 00:57:35,220
Judge Kang Yo Han is the only one who can stop all of this.

651
00:57:42,360 --> 00:57:47,170
But ... have I ever met you?

652
00:57:47,170 --> 00:57:50,320
You look quite familiar.

653
00:57:54,130 --> 00:57:57,470
You investigated Assemblyman Jo San.

654
00:57:59,610 --> 00:58:02,000
Do you remember?

655
00:58:08,320 --> 00:58:11,450
The one that committed suicide after being framed by you.

656
00:58:14,490 --> 00:58:17,430
I was in middle school at that time.

657
00:58:20,890 --> 00:58:26,470
Were you? Did he have a son?

658
00:58:35,730 --> 00:58:38,620
You look a lot like your father.

659
00:58:59,060 --> 00:59:01,120
Who is there?

660
00:59:10,620 --> 00:59:15,170
I thought you might want to see me by now. Or not?

661
00:59:20,670 --> 00:59:24,510
Because of Do Yeong Chun, the man you switched out,

662
00:59:24,510 --> 00:59:27,550
I lost my parents.

663
00:59:29,900 --> 00:59:34,750
I don't expect something like an apology or remorse.

664
00:59:36,010 --> 00:59:41,210
Please cooperate so that we can capture the bigger criminals.

665
00:59:50,370 --> 00:59:57,190
Are you saying you'll pardon me if I become a whistle-blower?

666
00:59:57,190 --> 01:00:00,170
Is there any other way for you?

667
01:00:43,310 --> 01:00:47,730
I want to consider it while I smoke this.

668
01:00:49,350 --> 01:00:52,370
Could you step out for a moment?

669
01:01:23,800 --> 01:01:27,500
Ministry of Justice

670
01:01:28,610 --> 01:01:30,990
Let me check your ID.

671
01:01:31,870 --> 01:01:34,510
I am Lieutenant Yun Su Hyeon of the Metropolitan Investigation Unit.

672
01:01:35,620 --> 01:01:37,390
It's confirmed.

673
01:01:41,700 --> 01:01:45,100
2nd Floor: Minister's Office

674
01:01:45,100 --> 01:01:47,200
Under construction

675
01:03:16,630 --> 01:03:18,620
Yeong Min,

676
01:03:22,700 --> 01:03:24,330
come here.

677
01:03:25,370 --> 01:03:27,300
Come on.

678
01:03:37,400 --> 01:03:42,500
I'm sorry, Mom. I'm sorry.

679
01:04:17,570 --> 01:04:19,510
Yeong Min ...

680
01:05:28,860 --> 01:05:30,780
Minister ...

681
01:05:39,040 --> 01:05:44,330
We must hurry to find the files first.

682
01:06:02,130 --> 01:06:04,980
Put your hands up and back away.

683
01:06:10,160 --> 01:06:12,010
Kang Yo Han?

684
01:06:22,370 --> 01:06:24,600
Just back away.

685
01:06:30,620 --> 01:06:33,740
You, get up from there. Quickly get up.

686
01:06:53,880 --> 01:06:55,830
S-Su Hyeon.

687
01:07:05,680 --> 01:07:10,650
Devil Judge Preview
We thank actor Jeong Eun Pyo for his special appearence.

688
01:07:38,100 --> 01:07:42,470
I want you to be lonely like me.

689
01:07:42,470 --> 01:07:44,880
The lengths I am going to help you!

690
01:07:44,880 --> 01:07:46,410
Please leave Ga On alone.

691
01:07:46,410 --> 01:07:49,410
Please cut Yun Su Hyeon out of your life.

692
01:07:49,410 --> 01:07:52,360
There still is a threat to the foundation.

693
01:07:52,360 --> 01:07:56,030
As a Supreme Court Justice I am calling for disbanding of the people's court.

694
01:07:56,030 --> 01:07:57,470
Let's move on with it.

695
01:07:57,470 --> 01:07:59,170
He's attempting something big.

696
01:07:59,200 --> 01:08:02,800
- Are you afraid?
- Does the fight right now feel like a joke?!

697
01:08:02,830 --> 01:08:04,040
What are you doing?

698
01:08:04,040 --> 01:08:07,140
You also have to go to rescue Judge Kim Ga On.

699
01:08:07,140 --> 01:08:08,880
You can't!
